# ホストとゲストでコピペする
## Reference
- https://unix.stackexchange.com/questions/109117/virt-manager-copy-paste-functionality-to-the-vm
https://voxelmanip.se/2022/07/12/Setting-Up-Android-x86-With-Virt-Manager/

You have to use "Spice" instead of "VNC" :
クライアント側に､spice-gtkが必要だが､virt-managerにはデフォルトで入っている｡

必須
ゲストで､spice-vdagentをインストールし､サービスをスタートさせる｡
reboot
----

virt-manager has now a spice-gtk client built-in. 
	But you need to install python-spice-client-gtk (spice-client-gtk on debian) on the VM host
	If you use virt-manager on another machine to connect to the VM host remotely through ssh, you must also install python-spice-client-gtk on that machine

1. Connect to your VM guest (with ssh) ; 
         in the guest, install spice-vdagent and verify that spice-vdagentd is launched
         (ps -lef|grep spice-vdagentd will return you the process if its running)
2. Show virtual hardware details
	3. already set as default, Select Display VNC, change VNC to Spice and accept to add the Channel
	4. may not need, Change the Video model from Cirrus (the default) to QXL
5. Restart virt-manager and power on the virtual machine
You are using Spice.


## Another solution, without X, but assuming that you are able to ssh to your host from your machine, and to your VM from your host :
mymachine:~$ssh user@host
host:~$ssh user@guest


